WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:04.585
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

00:16.417 --> 00:19.820
NARRATOR:
<i>It was late Christmas Eve,
</i> <i>and all through the house,</i>

00:19.887 --> 00:21.555
<i>all the creatures
</i> <i>were stirring,</i>

00:21.622 --> 00:23.624
<i>every witch, cat and mouse.</i>

00:23.691 --> 00:26.327
<i>Jerry dressed up his
</i> <i>home with holiday cheer,</i>

00:26.394 --> 00:30.064
<i>knowing that Santa Claus
</i> <i>soon would be here.</i>

00:30.131 --> 00:32.868
<i>Hildy rolls dough
</i> <i>while Beatie stamps them out.</i>

00:32.934 --> 00:37.004
<i>Cookies sprinkled with
</i> <i>gremlin hair, rump scabs
</i> <i>and fresh troll snot.</i>

00:37.071 --> 00:40.107
<i>Don't forget the donkey
</i> <i>dandruff or cockroach meat.</i>

00:40.174 --> 00:42.676
<i>Then bake them
</i> <i>on a dirty cookie sheet.</i>

00:42.743 --> 00:44.979
<i>Witchy treats
</i> <i>no one else dare eat.</i>

00:45.046 --> 00:50.046
<i>-Just for Santa,
</i> <i>isn't that sweet?
-(FLIES BUZZING)</i>

00:50.885 --> 00:54.635
-(THUDS)
-(PIANO PLAYING)

00:56.357 --> 00:59.960
<i>In the spirit of Christmas,
</i> <i>Jerry stopped all his teasing.</i>

01:00.027 --> 01:05.027
<i>And made Tom an offer
</i> <i>for this magical season.</i>

01:09.503 --> 01:11.003
(CREAKING)

01:29.890 --> 01:33.594
BEATIE:
Ooh, Hildy, just look at
the decorations.

01:33.660 --> 01:37.231
So beautiful, Thomas!

01:37.298 --> 01:39.466
HILDY: It just needs
one thing.

01:39.533 --> 01:41.468
(ZAPS)

01:41.535 --> 01:43.370
(FIRE CRACKLING)

01:43.437 --> 01:44.872
BEATIE: It's perfect.

01:44.939 --> 01:48.809
Hopefully, this is the year
Santa pays us a visit.

01:48.876 --> 01:50.411
(BOTH GASPING)

01:50.478 --> 01:52.579
NARRATOR:
<i>Then the witches
</i> <i>gasped and said...</i>

01:52.646 --> 01:55.316
HILDY: Wait, where's the tree?

01:55.383 --> 01:57.484
-(SQUEAKS)
-BEATIE: Where will
Santa Claus

01:57.551 --> 02:02.201
leave a present for me?
Uh, us?

02:04.658 --> 02:05.893
HILDY: No, Thomas.

02:05.960 --> 02:09.663
BOTH: We need a tree!

02:09.730 --> 02:13.333
BEATIE:
Oh, thank you, kitty dearest.

02:13.400 --> 02:15.903
(WIND WHOOSHING)

02:15.970 --> 02:20.174
Take my coat.
It's a little chilly.

02:20.241 --> 02:22.977
(WHISPERING)
I like a nice skinny tree.

02:23.043 --> 02:25.513
HILDY: This hat will keep your
head warm.

02:25.580 --> 02:30.580
(WHISPERING) Pick a nice,
big, plump tree, will you?

02:34.454 --> 02:37.424
(GASPS)

02:37.491 --> 02:38.691
(CRACKS)

02:43.597 --> 02:46.600
(SLAMS)

02:46.667 --> 02:47.867
(LAUGHS)

02:55.943 --> 02:57.477
(SHATTERS)

02:57.544 --> 03:00.181
(TEETH CHATTERING)

03:00.247 --> 03:03.817
NARRATOR:
<i>With the sisters' request
</i> <i>and a coat, oh, so warm,</i>

03:03.884 --> 03:08.456
<i>they set out for a tree
</i> <i>in the blistering storm.</i>

03:08.523 --> 03:11.325
<i>-Tom tries to think between
</i> <i>shivers and twitches.
-(SHIVERS)</i>

03:11.392 --> 03:13.994
<i>Which of the trees
</i> <i>should they bring
</i> <i>to the witches?</i>

03:14.061 --> 03:16.464
<i>Inside a pocket,
</i> <i>he found Hildy's wand.</i>

03:16.531 --> 03:21.531
<i>And a great idea
</i> <i>upon him had dawned.</i>

03:23.169 --> 03:24.069
(ZAPS)

03:30.243 --> 03:31.143
(ZAPS)

03:42.923 --> 03:47.462
(ZAPS)

03:47.528 --> 03:50.098
<i>Tom had his tree
</i> <i>when he heard from the roof</i>

03:50.165 --> 03:53.734
<i>-sleigh bells, a laugh,
</i> <i>and bold reindeer hooves.
-(BELLS JINGLE)</i>

03:53.801 --> 03:55.136
(SCREAMS)

03:55.202 --> 03:57.838
<i>The thump and the clump
</i> <i>and the fanciful jingle</i>

03:57.905 --> 04:01.009
<i>filled Tom with
</i> <i>an unusual tingle.</i>

04:01.076 --> 04:04.145
<i>And the sight
</i> <i>of Saint Nicholas
</i> <i>filled him with awe.</i>

04:04.211 --> 04:07.615
<i>Oh, how Tom wanted Jerry
</i> <i>to see what he saw!</i>

04:07.682 --> 04:10.585
<i>He jumped and he danced,
</i> <i>and he twirled,
</i> <i>and he pointed.</i>

04:10.652 --> 04:14.455
<i>If you saw him, you'd think
</i> <i>Tom was quadruple-jointed.</i>

04:14.522 --> 04:17.191
<i>But Jerry was still too
</i> <i>confused to respond,</i>

04:17.258 --> 04:22.258
<i>-till Tom pointed with
</i> <i>the magical wand.
-(ZAPPING)</i>

04:28.736 --> 04:33.736
SANTA: Hello. Anyone there?
Lights, please.

04:37.711 --> 04:39.513
Merry Christmas!

04:39.579 --> 04:40.914
(GASPS)

04:40.981 --> 04:45.981
Oh, did anyone else notice
that I'm a cookie?

04:46.053 --> 04:47.553
(GRUNTING)

04:51.459 --> 04:54.328
Mrs. Claus always said
I ate so many cookies

04:54.395 --> 04:56.731
that one day I was going
to turn into one.

04:56.798 --> 05:01.798
Now, be a good little elf
and turn me back, please.

05:03.236 --> 05:05.306
(ZAPS)

05:05.373 --> 05:10.373
Maybe it's the angle.
Have you tried...

05:17.017 --> 05:18.819
Can you imagine
why this might be

05:18.886 --> 05:21.556
a problem for a lot of people?

05:21.622 --> 05:24.958
NARRATOR:
<i>No visions of sugar plums
</i> <i>danced in Tom's head.</i>

05:25.025 --> 05:27.594
<i>He heard
</i> <i>disappointed voices instead.</i>

05:27.661 --> 05:29.496
(GASPS)

05:29.563 --> 05:31.531
(GASPS)

05:31.598 --> 05:32.967
(BOTH GASP)

05:33.034 --> 05:35.836
<i>As their Christmas exploded
</i> <i>like a peppermint bomb...</i>

05:35.903 --> 05:37.571
(EXPLOSION)

05:37.637 --> 05:39.406
<i>And they both knew who did it.</i>

05:39.472 --> 05:40.473
BOTH: It was Tom!

05:40.540 --> 05:42.843
Tom! Tom! Tom!

05:42.910 --> 05:44.044
(SHIVERS IN FEAR)

05:44.111 --> 05:46.146
WITCHES: Thomas.

05:46.213 --> 05:47.614
HILDY: Where are you?

05:47.681 --> 05:50.784
The tree, it's so lovely.

05:50.851 --> 05:53.654
(THUDS)

05:53.721 --> 05:57.425
You do understand
the urgency, right?

05:57.491 --> 06:01.195
BEATIE: Oh, there you are.
Santa should be here soon.

06:01.262 --> 06:03.097
HILDY: What a wonderful tree!

06:03.163 --> 06:07.063
Did you hear sleigh bells?

06:14.674 --> 06:18.724
Don't forget the ornaments.

06:21.950 --> 06:24.618
-BEATIE:
We can't forget our stockings.
-(GASPS)

06:24.684 --> 06:28.584
Hildy can use one of mine.

06:30.257 --> 06:32.526
Magic cookies for Santa.

06:32.593 --> 06:35.630
-This one actually rings
like a real bell.
-(DINGS)

06:35.696 --> 06:39.499
Santa wants yummy cookies,
not gimmicks, Hildy.

06:39.566 --> 06:41.368
Ho, ho, ho, ho!

06:41.434 --> 06:43.170
Merry Christmas!

06:43.237 --> 06:44.839
Oh, Hildy, really?

06:44.906 --> 06:47.508
I'm wondering if you might
be able to help me.

06:47.575 --> 06:51.545
BEATIE:
Santa's not going to eat
a cookie that talks to him.

06:51.611 --> 06:52.780
Well, that's true.

06:52.847 --> 06:56.550
But I will. (GIGGLES)
He looks delicious.

06:56.616 --> 06:57.617
(SCREAMS)

06:57.684 --> 06:59.721
(SCREAMS)

06:59.787 --> 07:04.787
I don't remember making
a talking Santa cookie.

07:07.061 --> 07:09.796
Enough, Thomas, I'm hungry.

07:09.863 --> 07:11.566
(THUDS)

07:11.632 --> 07:16.003
Come out, come out,
wherever you are,
little Santa cookie.

07:16.070 --> 07:17.537
There you are!

07:17.604 --> 07:20.941
(GASPS)

07:21.008 --> 07:22.876
(SLEIGH BELLS JINGLE)

07:22.943 --> 07:24.211
(GASPS) Is that him?

07:24.278 --> 07:25.780
HILDY: Were those
Santa's sleigh bells?

07:25.847 --> 07:27.916
BEATIE:
We need to get
to bed, sister. Now.

07:27.982 --> 07:30.818
HILDY: He won't stop
if he sees that
we're still up.

07:30.885 --> 07:33.087
NARRATOR:
<i>Tom has, oh, so much to do.</i>

07:33.153 --> 07:35.456
<i>Fixing Christmas for
</i> <i>you-know-who.</i>

07:35.523 --> 07:38.225
<i>But remember, Tom,
</i> <i>Blitzen means business.</i>

07:38.292 --> 07:40.727
<i>He's not fond of cats
</i> <i>who ruin Christmas.</i>

07:40.794 --> 07:42.796
-(GULPS)
-SANTA: Psst!

07:42.863 --> 07:47.368
Come, I have a new plan.

07:47.435 --> 07:49.503
You, cat,
will be Santa tonight.

07:49.570 --> 07:53.507
The magic of Christmas
depends on it.

07:53.574 --> 07:58.574
Perfect. Now grab the toys.
To the chimney we go!

07:59.580 --> 08:01.649
No, no, no.
The chimney, Tom.

08:01.716 --> 08:06.716
If there's a chimney,
you go down it.
It's tradition.

08:18.599 --> 08:22.570
-(SIZZLING)
-(SCREAMS)

08:22.637 --> 08:25.606
Well done, Tom.
It gets easier, trust me.

08:25.673 --> 08:30.673
Now on to the stockings.
Jerry, help him.

08:34.715 --> 08:39.715
What? They asked for the coal.
I can show you the letters.

08:42.490 --> 08:45.092
There's more in the bag.
Quickly now.

08:45.159 --> 08:48.159
Jerry, use the list.

08:55.735 --> 08:56.903
(SQUEAKS)

08:56.970 --> 08:59.070
Help him, Tom.

09:10.352 --> 09:13.554
NARRATOR:
<i>Now Tom went to the bag
</i> <i>to find Jerry's gift,</i>

09:13.621 --> 09:18.621
<i>but search as he did,
</i> <i>there was nothing else left.</i>

09:19.393 --> 09:20.828
<i>When the cat, no more naughty,</i>

09:20.895 --> 09:23.330
<i>changed his gift's
</i> <i>name tag, too,</i>

09:23.397 --> 09:26.033
<i>then the spirit of Christmas
</i> <i>came alive.</i>

09:26.099 --> 09:27.134
<i>Who knew?</i>

09:27.201 --> 09:29.503
Ho, ho... Whoa!

09:29.570 --> 09:31.372
You did it, Tom and Jerry.

09:31.438 --> 09:34.074
You awoke
the true spirit of Christmas.

09:34.141 --> 09:35.509
Well done.

09:35.576 --> 09:38.212
I knew you had it in you, Tom.

09:38.278 --> 09:40.814
I'll be needing that back now.

09:40.881 --> 09:42.583
(UNZIPS)

09:42.650 --> 09:46.387
NARRATOR:
<i>In a flurry of Christmas
</i> <i>magic, just as Santa demanded,</i>

09:46.453 --> 09:47.688
<i>Tom gave up the suit,</i>

09:47.755 --> 09:52.755
<i>-but was not empty-handed.
</i> -(GASPS)

09:55.829 --> 09:57.398
(SLEIGH BELLS JINGLE)

09:57.464 --> 10:00.401
<i>The sisterly witches
</i> <i>came charging downstairs.</i>

10:00.468 --> 10:02.503
Was it him? Was it Santa?

10:02.570 --> 10:05.307
He was here.
Yes, he cares.

10:05.373 --> 10:08.643
NARRATOR:
<i>Then the cackling girls
</i> <i>tore open their gifts.</i>

10:08.709 --> 10:13.709
HILDY:
It's the very first time
we made the nice list.

10:17.885 --> 10:20.721
NARRATOR:
<i>So listen up,
</i> <i>little girls and boys.</i>

10:20.788 --> 10:23.257
<i>If you think that
</i> <i>Christmas is all about toys,</i>

10:23.324 --> 10:25.259
<i>look at Tom
</i> <i>who learned something</i>

10:25.326 --> 10:26.828
<i>he'll never forget.</i>

10:26.894 --> 10:29.396
<i>It's not about getting
</i> <i>what you want,</i>

10:29.463 --> 10:33.534
<i>but giving what you get.</i>

10:33.601 --> 10:36.736
And that's the story
of Tom's Christmas plight.

10:36.803 --> 10:38.106
(CLEARS THROAT)

10:38.173 --> 10:41.908
May your New Year be happy.
And to all, a good night!

10:41.975 --> 10:42.976
No?
